"If students ask about `#![allow(dead_code)]` at the top of the exercise, it's necessary "
"because the only thing we do with the `Event` type is print it out. Due to a nuance of "
"how the compiler checks for dead code this causes it to think the code is unused. They "
"can ignore it for the purpose of this exercise."
